        "created_at": "2017-12-31T17:23:56.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote group-Grand_Cru_Cru\" data-username=\"NoahR\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/noahr/48/2194_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> NoahR:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Maybe the more interesting question is at what point does Vinous overtake WA for the kind of impact on pricing, availability and status of a wine/producer that RP had in his heyday, or has the moment where that can happen passed forever?</p>\n<p>Given that most of us chuckle bemusedly when some retailer advertises \u201c100 points\u201d and we subsequently see it\u2019s Suckling after we click (Bye, Felicia), and given that, say, Burlotto Monvigliero 2013 tripled in price after Galloni, I\u2019m wondering if that effect will carry beyond Italy\u2026</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>in terms of california wine, i think jeb will have more of an effect than AG.</p>",
